The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Justice turns fatal
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Justice turns fatal
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Patna, April 2: Two persons, including a 12-year-old, became victims of rage over trivial matters in the hinterlands of Bihar known of its lawlessness.         
	Pappu Kumars motorcycle hit a goat at Sugauli village in north Bihars Motihari district. The goat survived but the mob beat Pappu (22) to death. In another incident, Ramvilas Bhagat lost his cool over the loss of his cellphone, beating up his 12-year-old son to death in Purnea.        
	According to Motihari police, Pappus motorbike hit a goat straying on the Motihari-Bettiah highway at thickly populated Sugauli village around 7.30am. While the injured goat was lying on the road, the mob instantly attacked them with knives. Pappu died on the spot.        
	No one, however, had been arrested till evening.        
	In the other incident, Ramvilas beat up his son Sumit Kumar with an iron rod, suspecting him to have stolen the newly bought cellphone.                                                                                                                                                          
